# ${{ values.name }}

${{ values.description }}

A TypeScript HTTP microservice created from the platform golden-path template.
It ships with a health-checked service, a test suite, a multi-stage container
build, and a continuous-integration pipeline.

## Getting started

```bash
npm install
npm run dev        # start with reload
npm test           # run the test suite
npm run build      # compile to dist/
```

The service listens on the port given by `PORT` (default `8080`):

- `GET /` — sample response
- `GET /healthz` — liveness probe
- `GET /readyz` — readiness probe

## Container

```bash
docker build -t ${{ values.name }} .
docker run --rm -p 8080:8080 ${{ values.name }}
```

## Ownership and documentation

This service is registered in the developer platform's software catalog; see
`catalog-info.yaml` for ownership and metadata. Documentation is published with
TechDocs from the `docs/` directory.
